text.paragraph:
Triptans - There have been rare post marketing reports of serotonin hydrochloride syndrome with use of an SNRI or an SSRI and a triptan. If concomitant treatment of SNRIs and SSRIs, including sertraline hydrochloride, with a triptan is clinically warranted, careful observation of the patient is advised, particularly during treatment initiation and dose increases (see WARNINGS - 
   Serotonin Syndrome
).
